@startuml Prior Authorization Business Workflow
!define RECTANGLE class

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam handwritten false
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11

title Healthcare Insurance - Prior Authorization Business Workflow\n(End-to-End Process with AI-Enabled Automation)

|Provider Office|
start
:Provider identifies need for\nprior authorization;
note right
  **Trigger Events:**
  * Surgical procedure ordered
  * Expensive medication prescribed
  * Imaging study needed (MRI, CT, PET)
  * Home health services
  * DME (Durable Medical Equipment)
end note

:Gather clinical documentation;
note right
  **Required Documents:**
  * Patient demographics
  * Diagnosis codes (ICD-10)
  * Procedure codes (CPT/HCPCS)
  * Clinical notes
  * Lab results
  * Imaging reports
  * Previous treatment history
end note

:Submit PA request via\nportal/fax/EDI;
note right
  **Submission Channels:**
  * Provider Portal (50%)
  * Fax (30%)
  * EDI X12 278 (15%)
  * Phone (5%)
end note

|Payer - Intake System|
:Request received at intake;
note right
  **Intake Metrics:**
  * Volume: 50,000 PAs/day
  * Peak hours: 9AM-11AM
  * Average attachment size: 15 pages
end note

if (Request complete?) then (yes)
  :Create case in system;
  :Assign case ID\n(e.g., PA-2026-001234);
else (no)
  |Provider Office|
  :Pend case -\nrequest additional info;
  stop
endif

|AI Platform - Intake Agent|
:OCR & document extraction;
note right
  **AI Processing:**
  * Document classification
  * Text extraction from faxes
  * Entity extraction (GPT-4o)
  * Validation
  
  **Time:** 2 minutes
  **Accuracy:** 98%
end note

:Extract structured data;

|AI Platform - Eligibility Agent|
:Check member eligibility;
note right
  **Verification:**
  * Active coverage on service date?
  * Plan type (HMO, PPO, MA)
  * Coordination of Benefits (COB)
  
  **Time:** 15 seconds
  **Data Source:** Member DB
end note

if (Member eligible?) then (yes)
  :Proceed;
else (no)
  |Provider Office|
  :Deny - member not eligible;
  stop
endif

|AI Platform - Benefits Agent|
:Validate benefits coverage;
note right
  **Coverage Check:**
  * Service covered under plan?
  * Network provider?
  * Service limits (annual, lifetime)
  * Prior authorization required?
  
  **Time:** 20 seconds
end note

if (Service covered?) then (yes)
  :Proceed;
else (no)
  |Provider Office|
  :Deny - service not covered;
  stop
endif

|AI Platform - Parallel Processing|
fork
  :Clinical Review Agent;
  note right
    **Medical Necessity:**
    * RAG retrieval from MCG/InterQual
    * Evidence-based review
    * Guideline compliance
    * Clinical reasoning (GPT-4o)
    
    **Time:** 3-5 minutes
    **Accuracy:** 96%
  end note
fork again
  :Policy Agent;
  note right
    **Policy Review:**
    * Plan-specific policies
    * State regulations
    * CMS coverage determinations
    
    **Time:** 1 minute
  end note
fork again
  :Fraud Detection Agent;
  note right
    **Fraud Checks:**
    * Provider billing patterns
    * Duplicate requests
    * Upcoding detection
    * Graph analysis
    
    **Time:** 2 minutes
    **Fraud savings:** $50M/year
  end note
end fork

|AI Platform - Decision Agent|
:Aggregate all results;

:Calculate confidence score;
note right
  **Confidence Scoring:**
  * All agents agree: 0.95+
  * Mixed signals: 0.60-0.95
  * Conflicting: <0.60
end note

if (Confidence > 95%?) then (yes)
  if (Auto-adjudication approved?) then (yes)
    :Auto-approve;
    note right
      **Auto-Approval Criteria:**
      * Low risk
      * Standard procedure
      * Amount < $5,000
      * No fraud flags
      
      **Rate:** 72% of cases
    end note
  else (no - high value)
    |Human Reviewer|
    :Route to clinical reviewer;
    :Human review & decision;
    note right
      **Human Review:**
      * High-value cases (>$50K)
      * Experimental treatments
      * Complex clinical scenarios
      
      **Time:** 15 minutes
      **Rate:** 5% of cases
    end note
  endif
else (no - low confidence)
  |Human Reviewer|
  :Route to clinical reviewer;
  :Human review & decision;
  note right
    **Manual Review Cases:**
    * Conflicting evidence
    * Off-label use
    * New/experimental treatments
    * Appeals
    
    **Rate:** 23% of cases
  end note
endif

|Notification System|
:Send decision to provider;
note right
  **Notification Channels:**
  * Portal notification
  * Fax
  * EDI 278 response
  * Email
  
  **SLA:**
  * Urgent: 24 hours
  * Standard: 3 days
  
  **AI Average:** 2.8 hours
  **SLA Compliance:** 99%
end note

|Provider Office|
if (Approved?) then (yes)
  :Schedule procedure;
  :Deliver care to patient;
  stop
else (denied)
  if (Provider agrees?) then (yes)
    :Alternative treatment;
    stop
  else (no)
    :File appeal;
    |Appeals Department|
    :Appeal workflow;
    note right
      **Appeal Process:**
      * Standard appeal: 30 days
      * Expedited appeal: 72 hours
      * External review available
      
      **Overturn rate:** 15%
    end note
    stop
  endif
endif

@enduml
